args:
On New Year's Eve, a girl from the east named
Botan rushes into the Halidom, followed shortly
by a group of fiends she'd been battling. In the
midst of the chaos, a man named Ieyasu—who
is the leader of one of the Twelve Wyrmclans—
also shows up to lend a hand.
It's time for one final deep cleaning\nbefore we put this year to bed.
The prince and Luca will tackle the\nstoreroom, Ranzal the courtyard,\nMym the hall, and Elisanne the larder.
No no! This grouping will never do!\nI want to be with my darling!
And I gotta clean the whole courtyard\nby myself?! That thing's HUGE!
Stop being selfish and lend a hand,\nall of you.
This castle is quite large, as you know.\nIf we don't divide the work up properly,\nthe new year will arrive before we finish.
What about me, Cleo? I wanna help!
Hmm... Well, perhaps you can clean all\nthe places other people can't reach.
You got it, sister! Those dust bunnies won't\nknow what hit 'em once I'm through.
And when you finish cleaning your area,\nplease go pitch in elsewhere.
Now hop to it! Chop chop!
Cleo? We finished cleaning the storeroom.
Where do you want us to toss the trash?
You can gather it up near the hallway\nentrance for now, thank you.
All right, break time at las—Huh?
Hmm... Now that you mention it,\nit sounds like someone running\ntoward our current locati—
Um, Luca? Am I wrong, or is that woman\ncharging directly at us?
She's gonna slam right into us! RUUUN!
What in heaven's name is going on here?!
Oh, blech! Who the heck dropped a pile of\nstinky garbage here?!
Wait, no. Never mind. Doesn't matter.\nYou guys better hold on to your butts,\nbecause I'm gonna THRASH you!
You're the one who needs a firm grip on\nher cheeks, madam. How dare you run\ninto our home spouting threats!
Oh dear. There goes the garbage pile.
Well, you've scattered it everywhere.\nAre you pleased with yourself now?
Hey, YOU'RE the one who left a pile of\ncrap in the hallway!
And aren't you the one who ran into it?\nNow take responsibility for your deed\nand clean it up at once.
I'll clean YOU up! ...Wait, that makes no\nsense. Anyway, forget it—I'm too busy to\nbe sweeping up trash!
...There. It's done. Sorry again for\nmaking a mess of everything.
Urgh. How did it come to this...?
Er, if I can interrupt, what is your name\nand where are you from?
It's an island nation located waaay\neast of here. It's all the way across the\ncontinent, actually.
Wait, so you crossed the sea to get here?!
Whatever brings you such a distance?
Right! That. So um, is there perchance\nsomeone in this castle claiming to be\nthe head of one of the Twelve Wyrmclans?
Doubtful, considering I've never heard\nof the Twelve Wyrmclans before this\nvery moment. What are they exactly?

They are the successors to the shogunate,
the government that rules Hinomoto.
The head of the shogunate is called the
＂shogun＂—basically the head general.
The shogunate is a military form of\ngovernment, then?
Essentially, yeah. But the shogun isn't\nJUST a military leader.
I guess you'd say he's kind of like a king.
Wait—how is he ＂kind of like＂ a king?\nWhat does that mean?
Ah, right. You see, Hinomoto is a nation\nruled by both dragons AND humans.
How the heck does THAT work?!
Easy! A dragon named Amaterasu rules\nover the other dragons, while the shogun\ncommands all of the humans.
Although Amaterasu really only acts when\nthe nation is in some kind of danger.
The day-to-day aspects of ruling are all\ncarried out by the shogun—who Amaterasu\nappoints to the position, by the way.
I see... So the shogun is only ＂kind of like＂\na king because he shares his power with\nthe ruler of dragons. One half of the whole.
And the people who can become shogun\ncome from one of the Twelve Wyrmclans?
So they're basically all just like\n{player_name}!
We got a horde'a fiends incomin' here,\nand they're incomin' fast!
Oh, poo. They must have followed me.
Like I said, I came to this castle because\nI thought someone from the Twelve\nWyrmclans might be here.
But while I was traveling this stupid\nfiend nest got in my way and I kinda\nsorta...smashed it up real good.
Well, that would certainly explain their\ncurrent displeasure.
We can't let them into the castle—we\nhave to go outside and intercept them!
Nice job, lady! Next time, maybe DON'T\ngo pissin' off a whole barrel'a fiends,\nyeah?!
This is their fault for building that stupid\nnest right in my way!
If the two of you have breath to spare\nfor bickering, you can fight harder!
They don't seem to be slowing down.\nIt might be time for me to shapeshift...
Addis? Sazanka? Take care of this.
Tch! Persistent little curs, ain't they?
My lord has commanded us take care of\nthese foes, and we shall see his will done.
People of Alberia! We shall aid you!
Maybe stop with the fancy intros for a sec\nand LOOK BEHIND YA!
Another horde of them is about to—
How rude to deny us the chance to speak\nour names before battle.
I am Ieyasu, head of one of the\nTwelve Wyrmclans!
I come forth bearing the strength of\nMarishiten, to whom I have sworn\nmy soul.
I'll end this fool's game now...\nDaybreak Flurry!
He slayed all the remaining fiends!\nAmazing!
Did he just turn into a dragon?!
Yep. He's got the gift of transformation.
This is Master Ieyasu, head of one of our\nTwelve Wyrmclans, peerless warrior, and\nsuccessor to the shogunate of Hinomoto!
A warrior who can turn into a dragon and\nalso leads his people? Where have I\nheard this story before...?
Enough standing around all slack-jawed—\nwe got more fiends on the way!
Right. Let's mop up the rest!
